ESP32 Indoor Garden Controller - Setup Guide
==========================================

1. Install ESP32 Board Support
----------------------------
a. Open Arduino IDE
b. Go to File > Preferences
c. In "Additional Boards Manager URLs" add:
   https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
d. Click OK
e. Go to Tools > Board > Boards Manager
f. Search for "ESP32"
g. Install "ESP32 by Espressif Systems"

2. Required Libraries
-------------------
Go to Tools > Manage Libraries... (or Ctrl + Shift + I) and install:
- PubSubClient (by Nick O'Leary)
- ArduinoJson (by Benoit Blanchon)
- DHT sensor library (by Adafruit)
- Adafruit Unified Sensor (by Adafruit)
- NTPClient (by Fabrice Weinberg)
- LiquidCrystal I2C (by Frank de Brabander)

3. Board Configuration
--------------------
Go to Tools and select:
- Board: "ESP32 Dev Module"
- Upload Speed: "115200"
- CPU Frequency: "240MHz (WiFi/BT)"
- Flash Frequency: "80MHz"
- Flash Mode: "QIO"
- Flash Size: "4MB (32Mb)"
- Partition Scheme: "Default 4MB with spiffs"
- Core Debug Level: "None"
- PSRAM: "Disabled"

4. Hardware Connections
---------------------
Connect your sensors and actuators to these ESP32 pins:

Temperature Sensor (DHT22):
- Data Pin: GPIO4
- VCC: 3.3V
- GND: GND

Soil Moisture Sensor:
- Analog Pin: GPIO36 (VP)
- VCC: 3.3V
- GND: GND

LCD Display (I2C):
- SDA: GPIO21
- SCL: GPIO22
- VCC: 5V
- GND: GND

Relays:
- Fan: GPIO16
- Pump: GPIO17
- Light: GPIO18
- Fertilizer: GPIO19
- VCC: 5V
- GND: GND

5. Configuration Settings
-----------------------
Before uploading, update these values in the code:

WiFi Settings:
- // WiFi Configuration
  const char* WIFI_SSID = "YOUR_WIFI_SSID";        // Your WiFi name
  const char* WIFI_PASSWORD = "YOUR_WIFI_PASSWORD"; // Your WiFi password

- // MQTT Configuration
  const char* MQTT_SERVER = "d55d1972759041bf83d36d8d821741ab.s1.eu.hivemq.cloud";
  const int MQTT_PORT = 8883;
  const char* MQTT_USER = "indoor_garden_system";
  const char* MQTT_PASSWORD = "Hero4433>test43";

6. Verify your pin connections match the defined pins:
   - // Pin Definitions
     #define DHT_PIN D4              // DHT22 data pin
     #define MOISTURE_SENSOR_PIN A0  // Soil moisture sensor
     #define FAN_PIN D1             // Fan relay
     #define PUMP_PIN D2            // Pump relay
     #define LIGHT_PIN D3           // Light relay
     #define FERTILIZER_PIN D5      // Fertilizer pump relay

7. Then you can compile and upload the code to your ESP8266 using the Arduino IDE. The functionality will be exactly the same as with PlatformIO.